title: Tilicho Peak
text:
Tilicho Peak is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in the <a href="Nepal">Nepal</a>ese <a href="Himalaya">Himalaya</a>, near <a href="Annapurna">Annapurna</a>. The peak was first seen by Europeans in 1950 by members of the <a href="1950%20French%20Annapurna%20expedition">1950 French Annapurna expedition</a> led by <a href="Maurice%20Herzog">Maurice Herzog</a> who were attempting to find Annapurna I.
<a href="Tilicho%20Lake">Lake Tilicho</a> is located on the northern side of the peak.
The first ascent was made in 1978 by the French climber <a href="Emanuel%20Schmutz">Emanuel Schmutz</a> using the northwest shoulder.
